<h1 id=3D"galaxymakercheckerwidgetexpv1-4.Capability:ToUpdate/Patchtheappro=
valworkflowbasedonuser's(checker's)consent"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43=
,77);">4. Capability: To Update/Patch the approval workflow based on user's=
(checker's) consent</span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"galaxymakercheckerwidgetexpv1-POST/approvalWorkflowConsent"><span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">POST /approvalWorkflowConsent</span><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">&nbsp;</span></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">This is a dummy endpoint to help P=
DP identify an authorisation consent API call is triggered/dispatched, so t=
hat PDP can then initiate the maker-checker consent process accordingly. Th=
is route will not include any business logic and will return 204(No Content=
) without any response body, however, when PEP(Ping Access GW) intercepts t=
his API call as part of maker-checker process, it will return 200 status co=
de with the response payload as defined in the Response section.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
