<h3 id=3D"galaxymakercheckerwidgetexpv1-4.3.InputValidation">4.3. Input Val=
idation</h3>
<p>This route will handle the following request validations,&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 716=
.097px;" data-snooker-col-series=3D"numbers" data-snooker-locked-cols=3D"0"=
>
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 31.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 269.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 220.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 195.0px;">
</colgroup>
<thead class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh" style=3D"text-align: left;vertic=
al-align: top;" contenteditable=3D"false" data-mce-resize=3D"false"><br></t=
h>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p><br></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p><br></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTh">=
<p><br></p></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" style=3D"text-align: left;vertic=
al-align: top;" contenteditable=3D"false" data-mce-resize=3D"false">1</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>The request body should contain the following mandatory attributes,</p>
<ul>
<li>approvalWorkflowId</li>
<li>status</li>
<li><pre>entitlementsPayload</pre></li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Return 400</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" rowspan=3D"2" class=3D"=
confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><u><strong>Note:</strong=
></u></span> These validations will have to happen at the PDP end(and not i=
n the Widget Exp API route) as PDP will intercept the request for processin=
g.&nbsp;<br><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong><br></strong></spa=
n></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" style=3D"text-align: left;vertic=
al-align: top;" contenteditable=3D"false" data-mce-resize=3D"false">2</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
<p>The "description" attribute/property under comment object should be vali=
dated for any ISG vulnerable characters.&nbsp;</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">=
Return 400</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"galaxymakercheckerwidgetexpv1-5.Capability:GETapprovalworkflowdet=
ailsforaspecificapprovalworkflowid"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">5=
. Capability: GET approval workflow details for a specific approval workflo=
w id</span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"galaxymakercheckerwidgetexpv1-GET/approvalWorkflowDetails"><span =
style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">GET /approvalWorkflowDetails</span><span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">&nbsp;</span></h2>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">This end point will get the workfl=
ow details for the supplied approval workflow id.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0)=
;"><u><strong>Feb 2026 ERM changes associated with divisions:</strong></u><=
/span> <span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">As part of divisions feature, C=
hannels is expected to display the division name for payments, transfers &a=
mp; add beneficiary sub type workflow requests if a divisionId is associate=
d with the maker EXP API request. To meet to this requirement, the endpoint=
 will be extended to query PDP to fetch the divisions associated with a mak=
er userId to filter and fetch the division name. The sequence flow for this=
 requirement can be found here :</span> <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.w=
estpac.com.au/display/ARTC/SD%3A+Sub-Orgs%28Divisions%29+Channels#SD:SubOrg=
s(Divisions)Channels-PaymentDetails-Authorisation" rel=3D"nofollow">SD: Sub=
-Orgs(Divisions) Channels - PaymentDetails-Authorisation</a></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77=
);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><u><strong>May 2026 ERM changes as=
sociated with Confirmation of Payee:</strong></u></span> <span style=3D"col=
or: rgb(255,0,0);">As part of CoP feature, Channels is expected to display =
the CoP validation outcome for payments, add beneficiary &amp; update benef=
iciary sub type workflow requests, if CoP matched status code is included a=
s part of the maker EXP API request. To meet to this requirement, the endpo=
int will be extended to include CoP matched status code as part of the resp=
onse, as per the SD here:</span> <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.=
com.au/display/ARTC/06+-+SD%3A+Confirmation+of+payee#id-06SD:Confirmationof=
payee-Sequenceflowdiagram" rel=3D"nofollow">06 - SD: Confirmation of payee =
- Sequenceflowdiagram</a></span></span></p>
