<td style=3D"text-align: left;vertical-align: top;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><u><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>Feb 2026 ERM divisions c=
hanges:</strong></span></u>&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"> <sp=
an style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">As part of divisions feature, Channels is=
 expected to display the division name for payments, transfers &amp; add be=
neficiary sub type workflow requests if a divisionId is associated with the=
 maker EXP API json request payload. To meet to this requirement, the endpo=
int will be extended to query PDP to fetch the divisions associated with a =
maker userId to filter and fetch the division name. The division name will =
then be returned as part of the EXP API response(refer to the sample respon=
se highlighted with Feb 2026 ERM changes for the response attribute name).<=
/span></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0)=
;"><u><strong>May 2026 ERM changes associated with Confirmation of Payee:</=
strong></u></span> <span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">As part of CoP feat=
ure, Channels is expected to display the CoP validation outcome for payment=
s, add beneficiary &amp; update beneficiary sub type workflow requests, if =
CoP matched status code is included as part of the maker EXP API request. T=
o meet to this requirement, the endpoint will be extended to include CoP ma=
tched status code as part of the response.</span></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>The downstream DSR CAP API will return the following response which will=
 hold the Exp API payload(payments/beneficiary Exp API request payload) und=
er "additionalInformation" object. The "additionalInformation" object has a=
n attribute/property called "entitlementPayload" which will hold the Exp AP=
I request Payload as Json string. &nbsp;This Widget Exp API route will have=
 to deserialise the Exp API Payload json object held within data[i].additio=
nalInformation.entitlementPayload.makerRequest.payload into appropriate pay=
loads(payments payload or beneficiary payload) based on the SubType.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p><u><strong>Note: </strong></u>The above deserialisation approach will be=
 adopted only for Payments and Beneficiary type/subtype, for any other type=
/subtype(to support staff requirements), the Exp API will not deserialise t=
he Exp API Payload json object held within the data[i].additionalInformatio=
n.entitlementPayload.makerRequest.payload, instead it will just return the =
Exp API json mapped against "payloadString" attribute in the Exp API respon=
se</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><br></p>
