<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);"><strong>Feb 2026 ERM divisions cha=
nges:</strong></span>&nbsp;<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"> <span sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(255,0,0);">As part of divisions feature, Channels is expec=
ted to display the division name for payments, transfers &amp; add benefici=
ary sub type workflow requests if a divisionId is associated with the maker=
 EXP API json request payload. To meet to this requirement, the endpoint wi=
ll be extended to query PDP to fetch the divisions associated with a maker =
userId to filter and fetch the division name. The sequence flow for this re=
quirement can be found here :</span> <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.west=
pac.com.au/display/ARTC/SD%3A+Sub-Orgs%28Divisions%29+Channels#SD:SubOrgs(D=
ivisions)Channels-PaymentDetails-Authorisation" rel=3D"nofollow">SD: Sub-Or=
gs(Divisions) Channels - PaymentDetails-Authorisation</a></span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">PDP Query API: GetDivisionsFromPd=
pQueryResult</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">PDP Query API request: In the bel=
ow request, the following RequestAction should be passed based on the sub t=
ype</span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">If sub type =3D=3D "payment", the=
n pass RequestAction =3D "INITIATE_PAYMENT"</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">If sub type =3D=3D "transfer", th=
en pass RequestAction =3D "INITIATE_TRANSFER"</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">If sub type =3D=3D "addBeneficiar=
y", then pass RequestAction =3D "CREATE_BENEFICIARY"</span></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
